<item>
            <title>[FELIX-4422] Remove asynchronous starting of Jetty service</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-4422</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The Jetty bundle currently uses an &lt;tt&gt;ExecutorService&lt;/tt&gt; to start Jetty in the background. I&apos;m not sure this is actually needed with the recent versions of Jetty. I&apos;ve did a quick test to start Jetty synchronously in the bundle activator, but could not measure any significant timing differences in startup times.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A reason to change this is that it makes the start/stop behaviour bundle more deterministic when using it in integration tests.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12693921">FELIX-4422</key>
            <summary>Remove asynchronous starting of Jetty service</summary>
